nib.text:
A man was killed in a shooting Wednesday evening in south Minneapolis, police said.

MPD officers responded to a report of a person shot on the 1700 block of East Lake Street just after 6 p.m.

When they arrived, officers found a man, believed to be in his 30s, with a gunshot wound.

The man was pronounced deceased at the scene.

Investigators believe the victim was targeted. 

A police spokesman said there was no further threat to the public.

Police said a suspect fled the area and they were checking for video evidence of the shooting.

The investigation is ongoing.
